properties.Description:
(5/22/2014 8:15 AM DWC)
Wanted to bring the FMO up to date on a residence at 922 Harrison Street, that you maybe receieveing a phone call in the morning about. Last night Medic 1 was dispatched to an assualt call at the address above, where they found a 17 y/o female taking care of 5-8 children in a residence. Engine 1 was dispateched because the smoke alarm was continuing to go off but no smoke. E1 changed serveral batteries in the detectors but they continued to go off every 20-30 minutes. While in the residence it was noted to have very unkept areas and alot of drop cords going everywhere and alot of outlets near beds or mattrasses laying on the floor. Several areas of the residence had dog poop and clothing mixed together. EMS 2 came and started Child protective case, in which alot of problems within the structure where noted and multiple broken windows and/or blocked dooors were noted also. The occupant parent came from chalottesville, (Felica Garcia) will be calling about reentering the structure which B1 Lipscomb placarded due to safety, health and electrical problems. All children and 4 dogs were placed with other relatives or friends. The occupant Felica was returning to the charlotteville area tonight. The electrical meter was pulled and noted security device was replaced on the box. Multiple health and sanitation issues, children unsupervised that were smoking in bed and had multiple candles or scentsy items left on unattended were also found. house was placarded and electric meter pulled due to electrical issues. CPS involved as well and sounds unkept as well. I don't have any other info yet as well.
